{
  "$defs": {
    "InflationLag": {
      "description": "Publication lag for inflation index reference dates.\n\nInflation indices are published with a delay (typically 2-4 weeks). Securities\nusing these indices incorporate a lag to ensure the reference index is published\nby the settlement date.\n\n# Standard Lags by Market\n\n- **US TIPS**: 3-month lag (reference index from 3 months prior)\n- **UK Index-Linked Gilts**: 3-month lag (8-month for older issues)\n- **French OATi**: 3-month lag\n- **German index-linked**: 3-month lag\n\n# Rationale\n\nThe lag ensures:\n1. Reference index is published before settlement\n2. Index value is known at coupon payment date\n3. No estimation or forecasting required for payment calculation\n\n# Examples\n\n```rust\nuse finstack_quant_core::market_data::scalars::InflationLag;\n\nlet tips_lag = InflationLag::Months(3);  // US TIPS standard\nlet gilt_lag = InflationLag::Months(3);  // UK modern gilts\nlet no_lag = InflationLag::None;         // Inflation swaps (forecast-based)\n```",
      "oneOf": [
        {
          "additionalProperties": false,
          "description": "Lag by specified number of months.\n\nStandard: 3 months for TIPS and most inflation-linked bonds.",
          "properties": {
            "months": {
              "format": "uint8",
              "maximum": 255,
              "minimum": 0,
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "months"
          ],
          "type": "object"
        },
        {
          "additionalProperties": false,
          "description": "Lag by specified number of calendar days.\n\nAlternative specification for non-standard contracts.",
          "properties": {
            "days": {
              "format": "uint16",
              "maximum": 65535,
              "minimum": 0,
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "days"
          ],
          "type": "object"
        },
        {
          "const": "none",
          "description": "No lag applied.\n\nUsed for inflation swaps where forecast indices are used.",
          "type": "string"
        }
      ]
    },
    "PayReceive": {
      "description": "Direction for instrument legs (universal for IRS, CDS, variance swaps, etc.)\n\nFor interest rate swaps: Pay = pay fixed/receive floating, Receive = receive fixed/pay floating\nFor credit default swaps: Pay = buy protection (pay premium), Receive = sell protection (receive premium)\nFor variance swaps: Pay = short variance, Receive = long variance",
      "oneOf": [
        {
          "const": "pay",
          "description": "Pay the primary leg (fixed rate in IRS, protection premium in CDS, short variance)",
          "type": "string"
        },
        {
          "const": "receive",
          "description": "Receive the primary leg (fixed rate in IRS, protection premium in CDS, long variance)",
          "type": "string"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "$id": "https://finstack_quant.dev/schemas/instrument/1/rates/yoy_inflation_swap.schema.json",
